qas.question: The Vacuum state is considered what?
A typical vacuum cleaner produces enough suction to do what to air pressure?
The quality of a partial vacuum refers to what?

answers.text: how closely it approaches a perfect vacuum

qas.question: Outer space has a high quality vacuum with what equivalent?

answers.text: a few hydrogen atoms per cubic meter

qas.question: If all matter is removed from a vacuum, would it be empty space?
What does a few hydrogen atoms per cubic meter reduce air pressure by?

plausible_answers.text: how closely it approaches a perfect vacuum

qas.question: What does the quality of dark energy refer to?
What does lower amounts of dark matter mean?
In what century was dark matter discovered?

plausible_answers.text: one trillionth (10−12) of atmospheric pressure (100 nPa)

qas.question: What does dark matter usually operate below in space?
